  • Uses of ActionInterface in game

    Classes in game that implement ActionInterface
    Modifier and Type Class Description
    class  AttackAction
    Special Action for attacking other Actors.
    class  BreedingAction
    The action class for the activity of breeding between the dinosaurs
    class  DeathAction
    action for when the actor dies, it will remove the actor off of the map and add a corpse for the dinosaur of its species on the location that the actor died on.
    class  EatingAction
    the class for the action for the dinosaurs to eat food that they have found, it will remove the fruit or food item from the relevant location on the map, if the stegosaur eats a fruit on a bush the fruit will be removed from the bushes list of fruits and if the brachiosaur eats a fruit from a tree the fruit is removed from the list of fruits on the tree in a similar way and if the fruit or food item is on the map and is eated it is directly removed from the map.
    class  FeedAction
    the class for the feeding of a dinosaur by the player, it will heal the amount of food level from the dinosaur corresponding to the food item being fed.
    class  GrowingAction
    The class that "grows" the input dinosaur.
    class  LayEggAction
    A class for the dinosaurs to lay eggs.
    class  PickFruitBushAction
    A class to pick a fruit from the bush directly.
    class  PickFruitTreeAction
    A class to pick a fruit from the tree directly
    class  VendingAction
    class for the vending action that acts as a third party for the player to interact with the vending machine and buy items from what it has in store.
